# trovex write-guard zone franche — ONLY these .md STAY real files on disk.
# Everything else routes to the trovex store (trovex_write).
# Owner directive (2026-06-20): full-trovex, EXCEPT blog articles.
#
# Kept on disk for correctness (toolchain / harness / agents read these from
# disk — routing them to the store would break the repo):
README.md
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
SECURITY.md
LICENSE*
.claude/*
#
# Repo docs that live on disk for repo-readability (runbooks, marketing context):
.agents/*
docs/*
#
# Blog articles stay publishable source files (they ship as web pages):
**/blog/**
#
# Method canon ships as a web page (route /method), same rationale as blog:
growth/method/**
#
# Social drafts: copy-paste-ready files a human fires (specs, calendars, atoms),
# not centralized docs. Owned by social-lead, live on disk in growth/social/.
growth/social/**
#
# Process/governance docs: also live on disk for repo-readability; the canonical
# copy is mirrored to the trovex store (SSOT) per the growth/social precedent.
growth/process/**
#
# Launch kits: copy-paste submission payloads + per-registry/directory checklists
# a human fires by hand, not centralized docs. Owned by launch-lead.
growth/launch/mcp-registry-kit.md
growth/launch/wraith-mcp-registry-kit.md
growth/launch/free-tool-directory-kit.md
